Forecast based on: the short time frame, no major upset/announcement for the French economy and only the potential turbulence from Spanish politics.
Using 5% vol and expected return of 3%. Vol might be too low, but that is the trailing 30 days.

Over the next two-ish weeks it seems there are a couple different short term problems for the french markets. Specifically, Spain is a major market for french companies and there is plenty of political uncertainty at the moment plus an EU summit starting today that may take decisions on the UK, another major french trading partner.

Fairly steady upward trend since August. Expected strong YoY earnings performances for Q3 should drive the CAC 40 higher, but 5,400 looks like a pretty strong resistance level. Last October CAC 40 saw a 1.25% increase over 31 days. Same performance this October would put it around 5,417 at 10/31/17.
